行動
こうどう<sup>２</sup>【行動】 ﾛｰﾏ(kōdō)
〔目的ある活動〕 behavior; (an) action; activities; (a) procedure; proceedings; 《文》 conduct; doings; 〔実行〕 action; performance; execution; steps; a move; measures; 【軍】 operations; 【心理】 behavior.
〜する act; behave; take action; move; make a move; 《文》 conduct oneself.
▲単独で行動する　act ⌐independently [separately, on one's own initiative]; behave independently; go one's own way
・自主的に行動する　take action (by) oneself; take the initiative; go one's own way; 〔他者に頼らない〕 do not depend on other people
・慎重に行動する　act ⌐cautiously [with caution, with circumspection]; move carefully; be ⌐careful [cautious, circumspect]
・勝手に行動する　act ⌐on one's own initiative [without reference to other people]; take action ⌐by oneself [″《口》 off one's own bat]; make one's own moves; go ahead on one's own
・よく考えて行動しなさい.　Think carefully before you ⌐do anything [act, take action]. ｜ Look before you leap.
▲行動が大胆である　be bold in action; act boldly
・行動が機敏である　be prompt in action; act ⌐promptly [with promptitude]
・あいつは考えるより行動が先だ.　He doesn't think before he leaps. ｜ He doesn't ⌐plan [think] before he acts.
・彼は言葉に行動が伴わない.　His actions don't match up to his words. ｜ What he says and what he does ⌐are quite different [aren't the same thing].
▲(考えを)行動で示す　express [show] 《what one thinks》 by ⌐one's behavior [one's actions, what one does, the way one behaves]
・口で言うだけでなく行動で示してくれ.　Don't just say it. Do it [Put it into action] (and show me that you mean it).
▲謝罪の気持ちを行動に表す　show by one's ⌐actions [behavior, manner] that one is sorry
・(考えを)行動に移す　translate 《one's idea》 into action; put 《an idea》 into action; carry out [execute] 《a resolution》; act out 《a fantasy》
・緊急事態だから速やかに行動に移らなくてはならない.　This is an emergency, and demands immediate action. ｜ In view of the ⌐emergency [critical situation] we must hurry up and do something.
・絶えず彼の行動に注意していた.　I watched ⌐him [his behavior] carefully all the time. ｜ I kept an eye on ⌐him [his movements, his behavior, what he was doing].
・危険な行動に出る　do [undertake] something dangerous; make a dangerous move
・彼は思いがけない行動に出た.　He did something unexpected. ｜ He ⌐acted [behaved] unexpectedly. ｜ He made ⌐an unexpected move [a move I hadn't anticipated].
▲行動の自由を束縛する　limit [restrain, restrict] sb's freedom of action; tie sb's hands
・団体旅行だと行動の自由が制限される.　Group tours restrict your freedom of action. ｜ Going on a group tour means you can't do what you want.
・行動の自由が与えられる　be allowed freedom of ⌐action [movement]; be allowed to do what one wants
・行動の型　【心理・社会】 a behavior pattern.
▲慎重な行動を取る　act [behave] carefully [cautiously, with circumspection]; make a cautious move; take cautious steps
・軽率な行動を取る　act [behave] carelessly [rashly, without circumspection]; make a rash move
・独自の行動を取る　act ⌐on one's own [independently]; make an independent move; take independent steps; 《口》 go it alone
・…と行動を共にする　act with…; act together with…; cooperate with…; cast in one's lot with…; act in concert with…
・彼らは四六時中行動を共にしている.　They ⌐are [work] together night and day. ｜ They spend twenty-four hours a day in each other's company.
・行動を起こす　start action; set to work; make a move; 《口》 get down to ⌐work [it]
・今後はもう少し行動を慎まなければいけないぞ.　You'll have to ⌐be a bit more careful [behave yourself rather better] in future.
・行動を監視する　watch [keep an eye on] sb's movements; keep an eye on ⌐sb [sb's behavior, actions, what sb does]
・行動を束縛する　restrict [limit] sb's freedom (of action); tie sb down.
▲彼の行動は紳士的であった.　He ⌐behaved [acted] like a gentleman.
・彼女の行動は先が読めない.　You ⌐never know [can't predict] what she's going to do next. ｜ She's unpredictable.
